description: Returns a list of fleets. You can optionally provide filters to retrieve specific fleets.

parameters.name: nextToken
parameters.description: If the previous paginated request did not return all of the remaining results, the response object's nextToken parameter value is set to a token. To retrieve the next set of results, call ListFleets again and assign that token to the request object's nextToken parameter. If there are no remaining results, the previous response object's NextToken parameter is set to null.

parameters.name: filters
parameters.description: Optional filters to limit results. The filter name name is supported. When filtering, you must use the complete value of the filtered item. You can use up to three filters. (dict) --- Information about a filter. name (string) --- The name of the filter. values (list) --- A list of values. (string) ---

nested_items.name: fleetDetails
nested_items.description: A list of fleet details meeting the request criteria.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the fleet.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The time, in milliseconds since the epoch, when the fleet was created.

nested_items.name: lastDeploymentStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the last fleet deployment.

nested_items.name: lastDeploymentJob
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the last deployment job.

nested_items.name: lastDeploymentTime
nested_items.description: The time of the last deployment.
